Traffic Collision Data Analysis

My work consists of two sections:

  1. An analysis of demographics collisions by year of: age(min, max, avg), gender and background stats in R pulled from SQL Server.
  2. Time Series Forecast system to look into high collisions areas that might be of interest to reduce traffic accidents via law enforcement, additional traffic controller or other means mitigating the situation

Installing packages, creating the sql connection within R and ODBC and creating a basic select statement from SQL to test the connection

SqlStatement2 <- sqlQuery(con,'SELECT 
        YEARDateOccurred
        , VictimSex
        , VictimDescent 
        , MIN(VictimAge) AS YoungestAge
        , MAX(VictimAge) AS OldestAge
        , AVG(VictimAge) AS AverageAge 
    FROM (  
        SELECT
            YEAR(DateOccurred) AS YEARDateOccurred
            , VictimSex
            , VictimDescent 
            , VictimAge
        FROM dbo.TCD
        
        ) a
    WHERE YEARDateOccurred >= 2017
    GROUP BY 
        YEARDateOccurred
        , VictimSex
        , VictimDescent
    HAVING MIN(VictimAge) > 0 
    ORDER BY YEARDateOccurred, VictimSex')

Time Series Analysis

Most of the heavy lifting of the data were done in the backend; R was used to calculate the frontend of the Time Series Prediction.

This next SQL select statement is the dataset for the Time Series Analysis

Taking a look at the distribution and median of accidents

Boxplot analyis will determined which subset to investigate

Bagplot analysis shows points of where the majority of the frequency of collisions vs the collisions outliers

#con <- odbcConnect("Traffic Collision Data", uid = "supersql", pwd = "Admin12#")

SqlStatement3 <- sqlQuery(con,'SELECT 
        [Address]
        , YEAR(DateOccurred) AS YEAROccurred
        , SUM(Collisions) AS Collisions
    FROM dbo.CollisionTimeSeriesAnalysis2 
    WHERE YEAR(DateOccurred) >= 2017
    GROUP BY [Address], DateOccurred
    ORDER BY Collisions DESC--, DateOccurred')
  
#SqlStatement3

tapply(SqlStatement3$Collisions, SqlStatement3$YEAROccurred, mean)
##     2017     2018     2019 
## 7.986348 7.916339 7.951817
tapply(SqlStatement3$Collisions, SqlStatement3$YEAROccurred, median)
## 2017 2018 2019 
##    3    3    3
SqlStatement4 <- sqlQuery(con,'SELECT Collisions
    FROM(
        SELECT 
            [Address]
            , YEAR(DateOccurred) AS YEAROccurred
            , SUM(Collisions) AS Collisions
        FROM dbo.CollisionTimeSeriesAnalysis2 
        WHERE Collisions > 3
        GROUP BY [Address], DateOccurred
        --ORDER BY Collisions DESC--, DateOccurred
        ) a ORDER BY Collisions DESC')
  
SqlStatement4 <- suppressWarnings(as.numeric(unlist(SqlStatement4)))

#hist(SqlStatement4)

)
